It is 3 bushy plant, with leaves like those of rocket, but 3 little narrower, and with a seed like that of cress, being with honey very good for coughs and for expectora- tion of pus. It is also given for jaundice and for affections of the loins, for pleurisy, colio and coeliae troubles. It is applied moreover to parotid abseesses and to cancerous sores, in water or sometimes with honey to inflamed testicles, and is also very good for babies. With honey and figs it is used for com— plaints of the anus and for diseases of the joints, besides being when taken in drink efficacious against poisons. It also cures asthma, and fistulas also if mixed with old axle-grease‚ but care must be taken not to let the application touch the interior.
